      • validateArguments

        public void validateArguments()
        Validate the arguments after parsing, and throw a CommandLineException if: - Repeated raw barcode sequence tag(s) are found. - No valid tag name(s) are provided. In addition, it validates the raw barcode quality tag(s) and throws if: - Barcode qualities tag(s) were provided for no barcode sequence tag(s). - If barcode sequence and quality tag(s) have different lengths.

        validateArguments in class FixBarcodeAbstractArgumentCollection
